Prometheus exporter for OPNsense-specific metrics.

Runs a daemon that collects OPNsense-specific metrics (gateways, pf firewall,
Unbound DNS) and writes them in Prometheus format to the node_exporter
textfile collector directory.

WWW: https://brendanbank.github.io/banzai-plugins/releases/26.1/metrics_exporter.html

Changelog
---------

1.4.1_1

* Remove pkg update from post-install hook to avoid fingerprint errors

1.4.1

* Moved to banzai-plugins repository
* Updated package URL to banzai-plugins documentation

1.4

* Remove plugins fork dependency; use sparse checkout for build infrastructure
* Fix pidfile permissions for service status reporting
* Add pkg hook scripts for automatic plugin registration
* Add GitHub Pages pkg repo for firmware plugin info

1.3

* Run daemon as unprivileged nobody user (daemon -u nobody)
* Rewrite GatewayCollector to use configd Backend instead of PHP gateway API
* Replace config.inc with minimal autoloader to avoid config.xml dependency
* Fix .prom file ownership on upgrade from versions that ran as root

1.2

* Build non-devel packages
* Translate gateway status to human-readable labels
* Fix stale gateway config in long-running daemon

1.1

* Modular collector architecture with auto-discovery
* Add PF firewall collector (state table, counters)
* Add Unbound DNS collector (queries, cache, recursion, DNSSEC)
* Simplify status page to show raw Prometheus metrics
* Settings page with per-collector enable/disable toggles

1.0

* Initial release with gateway metrics collector
* Gateway status, latency, packet loss, RTT standard deviation
* Configurable polling interval and output directory
* Web UI with settings, status, and log pages
